[The number of countries reporting new outbreaks of measles is in decline in relation to renewed emphasis on all-inclusive vaccination programmes.

However, a consequence of the decline in measles vaccination (employing the almost universal triple MMR vaccine) may be an increased prevalence of of rubella virus infection and a concomitant incidence of congenital rubella syndrome. This situation is discussed in a letter to the editor of Eurosurveillance 2012; 17(10), 08 March from T Derrough, S Bacci, and P L Lopalco: http://www.eurosurveillance.org/ViewArticle.aspx?ArticleId=20106. - Mod.CP]
